    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix eval_and function returning incorrect boolean values\n\n### Summary\nThe `eval_and` function in the tracer filter module was not properly implementing boolean logic. When both operands evaluated to non-zero values, it was returning the actual value of the second operand instead of 1 (true). This caused inconsistent behavior in filter evaluations throughout the tracing system.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/filter/filter.c`: Modified `eval_and` function to properly return 1 for true and 0 for false, consistent with boolean logic and other filter evaluation functions\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may observe incorrect filter behavior when using AND expressions in tracer filters. Specifically, when both conditions in an AND expression evaluate to true, the filter may incorrectly evaluate as false if the second condition's value is interpreted differently than expected. This can lead to events being incorrectly filtered out or included in trace outputs.\n\nThe issue manifests when complex filter expressions using `filter_and` are evaluated, particularly when the second operand evaluates to a value other than 1. The filter system expects boolean 0/1 returns but was receiving the actual integer values from evaluations.\n\n"
}